    "Its userfriendly interface and wide range of functionalities make it a valuable resource for ML researchers and educators.",
    "KEEL provides pre-built, ready-to-use cost-sensitive versions of popular ML algorithms, namely C4.5 decision trees (Ting 2002), multilayer perception (Zhou and Liu 2006), SVM (Tang et al. 2009), and Adaptive Boosting (AdaBoost) (Sun et al. 2007)."
